The paper discusses a spam classification system based on a distributed hash table implemented using a structured peer-to-peer overlay. The focus of the paper is on developing a secure and efficient routing extension within the overlay. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Among these, cs.DC and cs.CR are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the paper's focus on developing a secure and efficient routing extension for a distributed system.
